genresAdvancedInfo.name: swiss classical piano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Swiss classical piano is a genre of classical music that focuses on solo piano compositions. It is characterized by its intricate melodies, complex harmonies, and virtuosic performances. Swiss classical piano often draws inspiration from the works of famous composers such as Mozart, Beethoven, and Chopin, but also incorporates elements of Swiss folk music and other regional influences.
